The paper deals with user modeling based on visual data, specifically photos and videos, on mobile devices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel user preference prediction engine that uses scene understanding, object detection, and face recognition, which are all common techniques in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also mentions the use of neural attention blocks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on user preference prediction also suggests that it may belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of a remote server for analyzing some photos suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
